    <div class="story-card__description">
                        <a class="story-card__series" href="https://www.propublica.org/series/no-defense">No Defense</a>
        
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/mississippi-courts-wont-say-how-they-provide-lawyers-for-poor-clients">
                                    Mississippi Courts Won’t Say How They Provide Lawyers for Poor Clients
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Six years ago, the Mississippi Supreme Court told judges around the state to file plans showing how they meet their obligations to poor defendants. This summer, amid increased scrutiny of public defense in the state, the first one was filed.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <span class="name">Caleb Bedillion</span>, <a href="https://www.djournal.com/">Northeast Mississippi Daily Journal</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-09-18EDT05:00">Sept. 18, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
        </p>

                <p class="story-card__unit">Local Reporting Network</p>
            </div>
</div>
                    


        
                    
<div class="story-card story-card--standard">
    
    

                    
                    
    
        <div class="lead-art">
            <a class="aspect-3-2" href="https://www.propublica.org/article/jefferson-parish-louisiana-three-strikes-habitual-offender-jeff-landry">
                <img
                    alt=""
                    src="data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%27http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%27%20width%3D%273%27%20height%3D%272%27%20style%3D%27background%3Atransparent%27%2F%3E"
