            </a>
        </div>
    
    <div class="story-card__description">
                        <a class="story-card__series" href="https://www.propublica.org/series/unwatched">Unwatched</a>
        
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/jefferson-parish-louisiana-three-strikes-habitual-offender-jeff-landry">
                                    He Fled a Traffic Stop in Louisiana. Now He’s in Prison for Life.
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            After 12 years behind bars, Markus Lanieux thought he had a deal for his release. Then Louisiana Attorney General Jeff Landry filed a legal challenge that could derail hope for those imprisoned under the state&#039;s &quot;three strikes&quot; sentencing rules.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <span class="name">Richard A. Webster</span>, <a href="https://veritenews.org/">Verite News</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-09-08EDT07:00">Sept. 8, 7 a.m. EDT</time>
        </p>

                <p class="story-card__unit">Local Reporting Network</p>
            </div>
</div>
                    


        
                    
<div class="story-card story-card--standard">
    
    


                    
    
        <div class="lead-art">
            <a class="aspect-3-2" href="https://www.propublica.org/article/how-chicago-cop-got-out-of-44-traffic-tickets">
